==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*murþa-'', from Indo-European ''*mr̥-to-'' ‘dead’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[morð]] (Dutch [[moord]]), Old High German [[mord]] (German [[Mord]]), Old Norse [[morð]] (Swedish [[mord#Swedish|mord]]).  The PIE root is also the source of Greek [[βροτός]] ‘mortal’ (earlier *μροτός), Latin [[mortis]], genitive of [[mors]] ‘death’, Old Church Slavonic [[мрѣти]] (Russian [[мереть]]), Lithuanian [[mirtìs]] ‘death’.  Compare [[morþor]].

